Class ParserLowerBoundedNodesNumberException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • services.xml.exception.ParserException
          • services.xml.exception.ParserSyntaxException

              • services.xml.exception.ParserLowerBoundedNodesNumberException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class ParserLowerBoundedNodesNumberException
extends ParserNodesNumberException
    This type of exception is thrown when the number of nodes of one type is wrong and the expected number is lower bounded. For example if a city map contained no intersections, whereas it should contain at least 2.
